---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About Calgary CX" description="Calgary CX is an independent CX insights platform by JP Sivasubramaniam — covering CCaaS, CX AI, AI Agents, Workforce Optimization, and Customer Service Operations.">

  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">About</div>
      <h1>Calgary CX</h1>
      <p class="lead" style="max-width:640px;">Independent insights on CX, CCaaS, AI Agents, and Customer Service Operations, written by a practitioner, for practitioners.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section>
    <div class="container--narrow">

      <div style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:2.5rem;">
        <img
          src="/jp-photo.jpg"
          alt="JP Sivasubramaniam — Calgary CX"
          style="width:100%;max-width:480px;border-radius:12px;box-shadow:0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.12);display:inline-block;"
        />
        <div style="margin-top:1.25rem;">
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jpsivasubramaniam/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-outline">
            Connect on LinkedIn
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="prose">
        <h2>Who's Behind This</h2>
        <p>I'm JP Sivasubramaniam, an Active CX Technology Learner and Enthusiast with 15+ years fully on the ground in contact center, unified communications, and customer experience modernization across consulting, product management, professional services, and managed operations.</p>

        <p>My career spans the full CX stack, designing, building, migrating, and optimizing contact center environments for some of North America's most customer-centric enterprises. I have worked with organizations ranging from mid-market to large-scale deployments of 12,000+ concurrent agents across telecom, financial services, healthcare, retail, and public sector verticals in North America and globally.</p>

        <p>I have held roles from consulting engineer through to architect, practice lead, product manager, and delivery manager, giving me a ground-level view of what actually works across the full lifecycle of a CX transformation, not just the strategy layer.</p>

        <p>My experience covers the breadth of CCaaS, UCaaS, and CPaaS platforms, AI-driven CX solutions across leading hyperscalers and best-of-breed vendors, workforce optimization, CTI, outbound lead management, and the operational complexity of managing large enterprise accounts through migration and beyond.</p>

        <p>Calgary has been my home for years and it is where some of my greatest opportunities and deepest learning in customer experience technology and transformation have happened. Calgary CX is where I bring that together, an independent space to share thoughts, content, and views that are genuinely relevant to CX leaders, practitioners, and peers navigating the same landscape.</p>

        <h2>What Calgary CX Covers</h2>
        <p>This platform publishes articles and videos across the enterprise CX landscape:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>CCaaS</strong> — Cloud contact center platforms, migrations, and vendor evaluations across Genesys Cloud, NICE CXone Mpower, Amazon Connect, and others.</li>
          <li><strong>CX AI</strong> — Artificial intelligence applied to customer experience, including evaluation frameworks, governance considerations, and realistic deployment expectations.</li>
          <li><strong>AI Agents</strong> — Autonomous voice and digital agents, operational model implications, and how to deploy them responsibly at enterprise scale.</li>
          <li><strong>Workforce Optimization</strong> — WFM, quality management, interaction analytics, and the shifting role of AI in agent performance programmes.</li>
          <li><strong>CX Strategy & Operations</strong> — Operating model design, client relationship management, managed services delivery, vendor management, and the strategic and operational decisions facing CX leaders today.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Who This Is For</h2>
        <p>Calgary CX is written for CX leaders, contact center operators, IT and procurement teams evaluating platforms, and anyone navigating the increasingly complex intersection of AI and enterprise customer service. Whether you're a CX director planning a CCaaS migration, a vendor trying to understand how practitioners actually evaluate your product, or an operations manager looking for a cleaner mental model for AI agent deployment, this is for you.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <div style="background:var(--mist);padding:4rem 0;">
    <div class="container" style="text-align:center;">
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Explore the Content</h2>
      <p style="color:var(--text-3);margin-bottom:2rem;">Articles and videos on enterprise CX, CCaaS, AI Agents, and contact center operations.</p>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap;">
        <a href="/articles" class="btn btn-primary">Browse Articles</a>
        <a href="/videos" class="btn btn-outline">Watch Videos</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>
